        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Alcazar of the Christian Monarchs</h2>
        <p>Not far from the Mosque-Cathedral is Cordoba's other most popular sight, the 14th century <strong>Alcazar of the Christian Monarchs</strong>. This incredible castle-like palace is also part of Cordoba's UNESCO world heritage sites and is known for its majestic gardens and fountains you can explore. The Alcazar also hosts outstanding views over the gardens and part of Cordoba's Old Town.</p>
    </section>



